        Epicodus
    .duration
      2015 (5 months)
    %p.job-description
      At Epicodus I learned full stack web development. I learned object oriented programming in depth with both Javascript and Ruby. Beginning with building simple test driven methods on the first day of class, I progressed to building complex Angular front-end applications backed by Rails RESTful JSON APIs. I became adept with the Ruby frameworks; Sinatra, Rails, and Middleman and with the Javascript libraries and frameworks; jQuery, Angular, and Ember.  I also became familiar with Structured Query Language, and with a group of fellow students built a Postgres backed Chess game during only the fifth week of class. Beyond languages I learned agile development concepts, how to talk about my code with other developers, and the importance of refactoring in maintaining a codebase.

    .job-title
